comments: Haliburton (IND) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
James (LAL) delivers contact to Nesmith (IND) that dislodges him from his position off ball.
The game is stopped due to a game clock malfunction and blue light signal. After correcting the clock and communicating with the Replay Center, the game resumes with IND retaining possession.
Beverley (LAL) and Turner (IND) reach for the pass and marginal arm to arm contact occurs.
Beverley (LAL) makes contact with the ball, dislodging it from Turner's (IND) control.
Hield (IND) places a forearm against James' (LAL) side and marginal body contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Nembhard (IND) reaches in and makes contact with the ball after James' (LAL) gather for the driving shot attempt.
Turner (IND) and Davis (LAL) come together in pursuit of the rebound and incidental leg to leg contact occurs.
James (LAL) dislodges Nembhard (IND) from his legal position under the rim, clearing space to receive the pass.
James (LAL) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Hield (IND) initiates contact with James' (LAL) left arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Turner (IND) maintains his right pivot foot prior to releasing the pass.
Turner (IND) turns to roll and incidental contact occurs with Westbrook (LAL) as he goes under the pick.
Westbrook (LAL) maintains his left pivot foot prior to releasing the pass.
James (LAL) and Nembhard (IND) engage and disengage under the basket and marginal contact occurs.
Turner (IND) maintains a legal guarding position on Davis (LAL) during his post shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) cleanly blocks Haliburton's (IND) driving shot attempt and incidental body contact occurs.
Turner (IND) commits a take foul on Beverley (LAL) as he is releasing the pass.
Turner (IND) and Davis (LAL) both mutually lock arms and quickly disengage during the rebound.
Beverley (LAL) commits a take foul on Haliburton (IND).
Nembhard (IND) releases the throw-in within five seconds.
Hield (IND) establishes his left foot as his pivot and maintains it.
Beverley (LAL) makes contact with Haliburton's (IND) hand while it is in contact with the ball and causes the ball to go out of bounds.
Schroder (LAL) rests a hand on Hield's (IND) front and marginal contact occurs during his jump shot attempt.
Nesmith (IND) and Davis (LAL) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
